## Frontend Rules (Next.js + React Testing Library)

### Stack

- **Vitest** or **Jest** — test runner
- **React Testing Library (RTL)** — query by what the user sees
- **MSW (Mock Service Worker)** — intercept `/api/repos` fetch calls
- Never test implementation details (state variables, function names,
  component internals)

### Test file location

```
frontend/
  __tests__/
    hero.test.tsx
    projects-grid.test.tsx
    about.test.tsx
```

### Test structure template

```tsx
// frontend/__tests__/projects-grid.test.tsx

import { render, screen, waitFor } from "@testing-library/react"
import { rest } from "msw"
import { setupServer } from "msw/node"
import ProjectsGrid from "@/components/ProjectsGrid"

const MOCK_REPOS = [
  {
    name: "ai-portfolio",
    description: "Personal portfolio with GitHub API integration",
    language: "TypeScript",
    topics: ["nextjs", "fastapi"],
    stars: 4,
    updated_at: "2024-05-01T12:00:00Z",
    html_url: "https://github.com/luisalarcon-gauntlet/ai-portfolio",
  },
]

const server = setupServer(
  rest.get("/api/repos", (_req, res, ctx) => res(ctx.json(MOCK_REPOS)))
)

beforeAll(() => server.listen())
afterEach(() => server.resetHandlers())
afterAll(() => server.close())

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// FEATURE: Projects grid renders repo cards from API data
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

test("projects grid shows repo name description language tag and github link", async () => {
  render(<ProjectsGrid />)

  // user sees loading state first (optional but honest)
  // then sees real content
  await waitFor(() => {
    expect(screen.getByText("ai-portfolio")).toBeInTheDocument()
  })

  expect(
    screen.getByText("Personal portfolio with GitHub API integration")
  ).toBeInTheDocument()

  expect(screen.getByText("TypeScript")).toBeInTheDocument()

  const link = screen.getByRole("link", { name: /ai-portfolio/i })
  expect(link).toHaveAttribute(
    "href",
    "https://github.com/luisalarcon-gauntlet/ai-portfolio"
  )
})

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// NOT COVERED IN THIS FILE — intentional v1 exclusions
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// - API returns empty array (empty state UI)
// - API returns network error (error boundary)
// - More than 30 repos (scroll / pagination)
// - Topics/tags overflow wrapping on small screens
// - Accessibility: keyboard navigation through cards
// - Accessibility: screen reader announces repo count
// - Dark theme color contrast ratios
// - Mobile viewport card layout
// - Loading skeleton animation timing
// - Performance: render time with 100+ cards
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
```

### RTL query priority (in this order)

1. `getByRole` — always preferred (accessible)
2. `getByLabelText`
3. `getByText`
4. `getByTestId` — last resort only, add comment explaining why

### What RTL tests must NOT do

```tsx
// WRONG — testing implementation
expect(wrapper.state().isLoading).toBe(false)
expect(component.find("ProjectCard").length).toBe(3)
expect(mockFetch).toHaveBeenCalledWith("/api/repos")  // internal detail

// RIGHT — testing what the user sees
expect(screen.getByText("ai-portfolio")).toBeInTheDocument()
expect(screen.getAllByRole("article")).toHaveLength(3)
expect(screen.getByRole("link", { name: /view on github/i })).toBeVisible()
```

