## Complexity Rule

> If the test is hard to write, the code is too complex. Simplify the code.

Signs a test is hard to write and what to do:

| Symptom | Diagnosis | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Need to mock 3+ things | Function does too much | Split into smaller functions |
| Test setup is longer than the assertion | Too many dependencies | Inject dependencies, simplify interface |
| Can't figure out what to assert | No clear return value or side effect | Make the function return something observable |
| Test requires deep knowledge of internals | Logic is buried | Move logic to a pure function, test that |
| Need to import half the app | Circular dependencies | Restructure modules |

For this project specifically:
- `GET /api/repos` must be testable by calling one endpoint and asserting one
  JSON shape — if it requires more, the service layer is too coupled
- `ProjectsGrid` must be testable by rendering it with mocked API data and
  asserting visible text — if it requires more, extract data-fetching from
  rendering

