## NOT COVERED — Project-Wide Exclusions (v1)

The following are explicitly out of scope for v1. They must not be tested now,
but every test file must reference this list so future agents know what remains.

### Error & edge cases
- GitHub API rate limit hit (60 req/hour unauthenticated)
- GitHub API returns 4xx or 5xx
- Repo with null `description`, null `language`, or empty `topics`
- Repo count exceeds GitHub default page size (30) or max (100)
- Network timeout between backend and GitHub API
- Postgres connection failure on startup
- Docker volume data corruption

### Performance
- Response time for `/api/repos` under concurrent load
- Frontend time-to-interactive with 50+ repo cards
- Cache query performance without index on `updated_at`
- Next.js bundle size budget

### Security
- GitHub token (if added later) must not appear in logs or API responses
- CORS policy enforcement
- SQL injection via query parameters
- Rate limiting on the FastAPI backend itself
- Secrets in Docker environment variables leaking to frontend

### Accessibility
- Keyboard navigation through the projects grid
- Screen reader announcements for dynamic content
- Color contrast ratios in dark theme
- Focus management

### Mobile / responsive
- Card layout on screens < 375px wide
- Touch target sizes
- Horizontal scroll on topic tags

### Operational
- Cache TTL expiry and re-fetch logic
- Graceful degradation when cache is empty and GitHub is down
- Zero-downtime redeployment on Vercel
- Docker container restart policy under failure